## 1. Legal Problems

### 1.1 Regulatory Risk (CRITICAL)

The app generates personalized buy/sell/hold recommendations based on user profiles
(risk tolerance, goals, holdings). Under the **SEC Investment Advisers Act of 1940**,
this could classify Finance Buddy as an **Investment Advisor**, requiring:

- **RIA (Registered Investment Advisor) registration**, or
- **Broker-dealer licensing** under FINRA

Calling the app "educational" does NOT protect us if the AI gives personalized stock
advice. Regulators evaluate what the software does, not how we label it.

Other applicable regulations:
- State securities laws (vary by state)
- FCA (UK) and MiFID II (EU) if expanding internationally
- GDPR / CCPA for data privacy (especially for minors)

### 1.2 What's Missing in the Code Right Now

| Issue | Location | Severity |
|-------|----------|----------|
| No Terms of Service page | Referenced in LoginPage.tsx signup checkbox but doesn't exist | HIGH |
| No Privacy Policy | Not implemented anywhere | HIGH |
| Age inconsistency: signup says 13+, README/Master Plan says 16+ | LoginPage.tsx vs README vs Master Plan | HIGH |
| No visible financial disclaimer in UI | Disclaimers only exist inside AI system prompt (chat.js) — users never see them | HIGH |
| No GDPR/CCPA compliance | No data export, deletion, or consent management | MEDIUM |
| No audit trail | Recommendations not logged for compliance | MEDIUM |
| Insecure JWT secret | Defaults to "dev-secret-change-me" in auth.js | MEDIUM |
| No parental consent flow for minors | Required if minimum age is 16-17 | LOW (hackathon) |
| No data retention policy | Chat history stored indefinitely in memory | LOW (hackathon) |

### 1.3 Recommended Fix (Hackathon Scope)

1. Add a **persistent disclaimer banner** across all pages:
   "This is an educational simulator. Not financial advice. No real money is involved. Paper trading only."
2. Fix the age requirement to **16+** everywhere (LoginPage.tsx, README, Master Plan)
3. Add a basic Terms of Service / Privacy Policy page (even a placeholder with key points)
4. Ensure the AI system prompt NEVER says "you should buy X" — always frame as educational

### 1.4 Long-Term (Post-Hackathon)

- Consult a securities attorney before any public release
- Determine if RIA registration or an exemption applies
- Implement full GDPR/CCPA data subject rights (export, delete, consent)
- Build audit trail for all recommendations served
- Add per-trade liability acknowledgment (double confirmation flow from Master Plan)

