## 2. Training Data for Financial Suggestions

### 2.1 Current State

The app uses **Claude API (claude-sonnet-4)** with prompt engineering. No custom model
is trained. The AI receives user context (holdings, budget, risk tolerance) and generates
responses. Without an API key, it falls back to hardcoded mock responses.

### 2.2 What Input Data Would a Custom Model Need?

If we build the ML recommendation engine described in the Master Plan, here's what
training data looks like:

#### Structured Data (tabular)

| Category | Features | Source | Volume |
|----------|----------|--------|--------|
| Price History | Open, High, Low, Close, Volume (OHLCV) — daily | Yahoo Finance, Polygon.io, Alpha Vantage | ~2.5M rows (500 stocks x 10 years) |
| Technical Indicators | RSI, MACD, Bollinger Bands, SMA, EMA | Derived from price data | Same rows, +20 columns |
| Fundamentals | P/E, EPS, revenue, debt/equity, market cap, dividends | SEC EDGAR, Financial Modeling Prep | ~400K rows (500 stocks x 40 quarters) |
| Macroeconomic | Interest rates, CPI, GDP, unemployment, Fed decisions | FRED (Federal Reserve) | ~180K rows (50 indicators x 10 years daily) |
| Sector/Index | S&P 500, NASDAQ, Dow, sector ETF performance | Yahoo Finance | ~36.5K rows |

#### Unstructured Data (text)

| Category | Source | Volume |
|----------|--------|--------|
| News headlines & articles | NewsAPI, Finnhub, Reuters | ~365K articles (100/day x 10 years) |
| Earnings call transcripts | SEC EDGAR, Seeking Alpha | ~8K transcripts (500 stocks x 4/year x 4 years) |
| SEC filings (10-K, 10-Q) | SEC EDGAR | ~4K filings |

#### Total Dataset Size

- Structured: **~3-5 million rows**, 50-100 features per row → ~2-5 GB
- Unstructured: **~375K+ documents** → ~1-2 GB
- Combined: **~4-7 GB** for a solid training set

#### Recommended Lookback Period

- Minimum: 5 years (captures one full market cycle)
- Ideal: 10 years (captures bull/bear/recovery/COVID/rate hikes)
- Maximum: 20 years (risk of outdated patterns; market structure has changed)

### 2.3 Model Architecture Options

| Model | Best For | Complexity | Hackathon? |
|-------|----------|------------|------------|
| XGBoost / LightGBM | Tabular buy/hold/sell classification | Low | No |
| LSTM | Time-series price trend prediction | Medium | No |
| Transformer | Long-range pattern capture | High | No |
| Ensemble (all above) | Production-quality predictions | High | No |
| Claude API + rules | MVP recommendations | Low | YES |

### 2.4 Hackathon Recommendation

**Do NOT train a custom model.** Instead:
1. Keep using Claude API with well-crafted prompts
2. Add rule-based signals (e.g., "flag stocks dropping >10% in a week")
3. Feed real market data into prompts so Claude can reason about actual numbers
4. Document the ML roadmap in your pitch as a Phase 4 feature

